JOHANNESBURG- The Free State provincial government in partnership with the Central University of Technology (CUT), will host the 4th Industrial Revolution Conference. The conference which will be taking place from the 28 – 29 in Bloemfontein, will be clearly focusing on 4IR technologies such as Artificial Intelligence (AI), Blockchain, Internet of Things (IoT), Big Data Analytics, Cloud Computing, Robotics and Automation,3D printing, Sensor Networks, etc. The summit will be covering the following Theme: Future of Mining, Agriculture and Agro-Allied Enterprises, Tourism and Hospitality, Healthcare, Manufacturing, Waste Management, Construction and Infrastructure Procurement, Education and Skills Development, Technology and Human Enhancement, Entrepreneurship and Innovation, Smart Cities, and Security. CLICK HERE TO REGISTER 